-- Colombian Stocks: Acerias Paz del Rio, Cementos Argos, Ecopetrol
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-04-26T20:40:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/colombian-stocks-acerias-paz-del-rio-inversiones-argos-exito.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.9 percent to 15,086.00, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.6 percent to 1,759.62.  Acerias Paz del Rio SA  (PAZRIO CB), a Colombian steelmaker,
jumped 11 percent to 32.10 pesos, the highest since March 27.
 Acerias Paz del Rio (PAZRIO)  will seek to sell about 9.05 billion shares,
and Grupo Votorantim, the majority shareholder, plans to
maintain or increase its stake in the company at the time of the
sale, according to a prospectus filed late yesterday on the
website of  Colombia ’s financial regulator.  Cementos Argos SA (CEMARGOS)  , the country’s biggest
cement maker, gained 0.2 percent to 12,000 pesos. The company
said first-quarter consolidated net income was 255.5 billion
pesos ($145 million), compared with 29 billion in the prior
year. Operational revenue increased 34 percent to 1.1 trillion
pesos, according to an e-mailed statement.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
gained 1.7 percent to 5,510 pesos. The company rose in line with
crude, which closed at a three-week high in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
